  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite the absence of citations and online discourse for the book \"Cold War Triangle,\" it stands out due to its strong commercial linkage, appearing on platforms like Amazon and Goodreads, indicating a level of interest and accessibility to a wider audience. The book has potential relevance to policy discussions, particularly in the context of the Sustainable Development Goals.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book \"Cold War Triangle,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2021, does not currently showcase any formal citations or online community discussions. However, it is noteworthy for its commercial linkage, being available on both Amazon and Goodreads, demonstrating a significant interest that may influence public engagement and academic discourse in the future.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Although there is no observed activity on platforms such as Wikipedia or Reddit, the book's presence in commercial markets suggests an alternative avenue for impact. This visibility could facilitate broader public conversations about the themes presented in the book, potentially resonating within academic and policy-oriented circles.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The absence of specific metrics detailing community engagement or scholarly citations may also present an opportunity for future research. Scholars can leverage this narrative to explore potential avenues of engagement for this work, particularly considering its implications for contemporary discussions about the Cold War's legacy and its relevance in today's geopolitical landscape.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The inferred strength of the book's policy relevance, indicated by a connection to one of the Sustainable Development Goals, underscores the importance of its themes in ongoing global discussions. As scholars and policymakers alike seek to understand historical contexts for contemporary challenges, \"Cold War Triangle\" may provide key insights for future inquiries, despite the current lack of explicit academic discourse surrounding it.</p>",
